fix: memory hooks had three bugs found by running an actual integration test against a live server on port 9999. (1) send_task model param was 'memory-recall'/'memory-remember'/'memory-consolidate' — not real model names. The harness passed them to the SDK which rejected them. Fixed by using agent_id as model name, which the harness maps to LLM_MODEL via the 'use_model = model if model != AGENT_NAME else LLM_MODEL' check. (2) XPRESSCLAW_PORT env var was never set in containers — MCP tools in mcp_memory.py/mcp_tasks.py used default port 8935, which fails when the server runs on a different port. Added to docker/images.rs env list. (3) HooksConfig issue already fixed in previous commit (serde skip + manual Default). Integration test evidence: agent responded, async remember hook created memory '[16e7ed06] User is Eduardo, loves hiking in Osaka' with tags ['inbox', 'personal-info', 'user-pref'].
